This paper deals with image segmentation using a convolutional neural network, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed solution involves pre-processing with a geodesic operator, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning for graph-based algorithms (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for segmentation, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of optimization techniques, which is a common topic in neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with the segmentation of histological images, which is a common topic in medical image analysis (cs.IR).
